File: The Fair Trade Independent Tobacco Association has taken government to court over the prohibition of cigarette sales. JOHANNESBURG - Government isn't being given more time to prepare its defence of the tobacco sales ban. Its second attempt at a postponement has been dismissed. WATCH: Mazzotti breaks his silence on tobacco ban The Fair Trade Independent Tobacco Association has taken government to court over the prohibition of cigarette sales. Government says a postponement should be granted because the country has now moved to Level 3. READ: BATSA to challenge tobacco ban But Judge President Dustan Mlambo says both parties agreed the matter would be heard in early June. If government still feels the need to apply for a postponement, it should do so in accordance with the rules of the court. The case is due in court next week. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.